<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1232,1761]" box="[151,1000,1232,1257]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Black, forewing with light brown caudal area. Tip of scutellum dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1232,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[199,371,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Caudal margin of pygofer rounded with long stout setae on caudal 0.33. Subgenital plate with long stout setae. Style linear with well developed preapical lobe, apical apophysis short, thumblike. Connective with arms shorter than stem. Aedeagus with well developed dorsal apodeme, preatrium short, shaft cylindrical, curved caudo-dorsally, apex with V- shaped notch; gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1232,1761]" box="[199,721,1412,1437]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[199,284,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Length.</emphasis>
